
[1]fallacy

   FAL'LACY, n. [L. fallacia.]

   1. Deceptive or false appearance; deceitfulness; that which misleads
   the eye or the mind. Detect the fallacy of the argument.

   2. Deception; mistake. This appearance may be all a fallacy.

   I'll entertain the favored fallacy.
